        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "3) testisDate(Zend_FilterTest)\n\"1997-07-16\" is a valid date\nFailed asserting that <boolean:false> is identical to <boolean:true>.\n\/home\/sebastian\/Work\/ZendFramework\/tests\/Zend\/FilterTest.php:180\n\n4) testTestDate(Zend_Filter_InputTest)\nFailed asserting that <boolean:false> is equal to <string:2007-01-01>.\n\/home\/sebastian\/Work\/ZendFramework\/tests\/Zend\/Filter\/InputTest.php:190\n\n5) testBasic(Zend_Validate_DateTest)\nFailed asserting that <boolean:false> is equal to <boolean:true>.\n\/home\/sebastian\/Work\/ZendFramework\/tests\/Zend\/Validate\/DateTest.php:82\n\n\nMost likely related to: gavin:\n* add getFixedDate(), remove auto-magic fixing of dates from getDate()\n* improved docblock\n* fixed but with 'a' am\/pm format specifier\n* improved diagnostics of getDate()\n* make auto-magic correction of invalid dates optional in _parseDate() (resolves ZF-883)\n* fixed bug in auto-magic correction of _parseDate()\n* added getDateFormat() to retrieve the default format string for a locale\n* fixed some unit tests\n* isDate() no longer returns true, if the input does not conform to the date $format (fixes ZF-882)"
