                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Issue related to ZF-882 \/ ZF-883.\nSee added comments there for further information.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-09T02:18:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-09T02:18:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12670",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "After looking in this I think the problems are related to this:\n\n3) testisDate\n\n -> always takes the standard locale. But the standardformat in different environments is not always as expected by this test\n\n -> always verifies strict... maybe loose checking should also be implemented\n(isDate -> strict, isFixedDate -> loose). 2000-01-10 is not the same as 01-10-2000.\nisDate gives false, isFixedDate gives true for such inputs.\n\n4) testTestDate\n -> see 3 -> locale and strict problem\n\n5) testBasic\n -> see 3",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-10T06:55:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-10T06:55:33.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12681",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I am working on some related issues that will address the date related issues above.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-11T18:39:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-11T18:39:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12709",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The issue of providing \"isDate()\" behavior involves many issues:\n# What date formats should be supported?\n# A locale is needed for proper interpretation\/normalization of dates containing month names.\n# Should  Zend_Validate_Date normalize month names (including abbreviated ones) in the input in order to parse the date?  Should this be done always, or only when requested?\n# What is the format of the date checked? (developer requested, default format for which locale?)\n# If the format defaults to the default format of the default locale, then the *exact* same \"is date\" Zend_Validate_Date check might succeed for one web visitor, but not for another from a different locale.  Is this behavior desired or should it be optional and only selected when explicitly requested by the developer?\n# Should Zend_Validate_Date require the developer to specify the date format?\n# Should Zend_Validate_Date require the developer to specify the locale?\n# Should Zend_Validate_Date indicate success for all dates that are valid, *after* checking for detectable errors, and correcting correctable errors?\n# Should the automatic correction above happen with or without the developers explicit consent \/ request?\n# Should Zend_Validate_Date even check dates in strings, or should it just wrap PHP's checkdate() function?\n\nThe Zend_Locale_Format::isDate() and isLooseDate() related functions are designed for quite robust operation, and might or might not serve the needs of Zend_Validate_Date, depending on the latter's requirements.  Clarification of requirements is needed before I can make recommendations for resolving the issues outlined above.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-13T13:04:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-13T13:04:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12711",
